===Etymology===
From {{inh|och|sit-pro|*d-kʷəj-n||dog}}; cognate with {{cog|bo|ཁྱི||dog}}, {{cog|my|ခွေး||dog}}.

This common Sino-Tibetan word has been replaced by {{och-l|狗}} in most topolects except Eastern Min, such as [[w:Fuzhou dialect|Fuzhou]] ''kēng''. In other topolects, this word is mainly found in compounds and not used alone.

