{{ja-kanjitab|いぬ|yomi=k|alt=狗}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*enu}}. Derivation uncertain. Various theories exist, including derivation from ancient verb {{m|ja|往ぬ|tr=inu||to leave, to be gone}}, from the way a dog will guard the house while the master is away; from a compound of {{m|ja|家|tr=ie||house, home}} + {{m|ja|寝|tr=nu||to sleep|pos=ancient monosyllabic form of modern {{m|ja|寝る}} ''neru''}}; from ancient Japanese {{m|ja|狗|tr=enu < wenu||puppy, dog}}, itself of uncertain derivation; or as a borrowing from some other unknown language.

